00:03:57.760 --> 00:03:58.850
not to reincorporate your

00:03:58.850 --> 00:04:01.410
Washington company into
Delaware.

00:04:01.410 --> 00:04:04.000
So there&#39;s a reason that so
many companies do it.

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:04.630
It&#39;s standard.

00:04:04.630 --> 00:04:05.430
It&#39;s familiar.

00:04:05.430 --> 00:04:07.200
So I&#39;ll tell you a story.

00:04:07.200 --> 00:04:10.430
We had a company at YC about
two years ago,

00:04:10.430 --> 00:04:13.580
that was originally formed as
an LLC in a state that I&#39;ll,

00:04:13.580 --> 00:04:14.920
that I&#39;ll say, Connecticut.

00:04:16.020 --> 00:04:18.080
The founders had some lawyer
friends there who said,

00:04:18.080 --> 00:04:19.730
this is the right way to do
it.

00:04:19.730 --> 00:04:20.400
And when they came to

00:04:20.400 --> 00:04:23.630
YC we said you guys need to
convert to Delaware.

00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:26.795
So the lawyers in Connecticut
did the conversion

00:04:26.795 --> 00:04:29.910
paperwork and unfortunately
they didn&#39;t do it right.

00:04:29.910 --> 00:04:31.610
They made a very simple
mistake but

00:04:31.610 --> 00:04:33.940
it was a very crucial mistake.

00:04:33.940 --> 00:04:35.760
The company was recently
raising money.

00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:39.210
Like a lot a lot of money and
this mistake was uncovered.

00:04:40.610 --> 00:04:43.030
That the basically the mistake
was this company thought it

00:04:43.030 --> 00:04:45.180
was a Delaware corporation for
a couple years, but

00:04:45.180 --> 00:04:46.870
in fact it was still a
Connecticut LLC.

00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:49.610
And I&#39;ll just say this four
different law

00:04:49.610 --> 00:04:52.020
firms were needed to figure
that one out.

00:04:52.020 --> 00:04:53.860
Two in Delaware one in
Connecticut,

00:04:53.860 --> 00:04:57.305
one here in the Silicon Valley
and the bill right now is at

00:04:57.305 --> 00:04:59.320
$500,000, for a conversion
mistake.

00:04:59.320 --> 00:05:02.000
So, so what&#39;s the takeaway
here, pretty simple.

00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:05.680
Keep it really simple and
familiar for yourself.

00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:08.250
The reason we incorporate all
companies the same way at

00:05:08.250 --> 00:05:10.140
Y Combinator is because it&#39;s
easy.

00:05:10.140 --> 00:05:11.170
So don&#39;t get fancy.

00:05:11.170 --> 00:05:12.540
Just save yourself some time
and money.

00:05:14.170 --> 00:05:16.330
&gt;&gt; Okay.
So once you&#39;ve decided that

00:05:16.330 --> 00:05:18.180
you&#39;re going to be a Delaware
corporation,

00:05:18.180 --> 00:05:20.540
how do you actually set that
up?

00:05:20.540 --> 00:05:22.890
And it requires a few
different steps, but

00:05:22.890 --> 00:05:24.610
the first one is actually
really easy.

00:05:24.610 --> 00:05:26.840
You literally just fax two
pieces of paper into

00:05:26.840 --> 00:05:29.280
Delaware saying, we&#39;re
going to set up a corporation.

00:05:30.730 --> 00:05:33.160
All that does though is create
a shell of a company.

00:05:33.160 --> 00:05:35.940
It doesn&#39;t actually do
anything within the company.

00:05:35.940 --> 00:05:36.790
So after that,

00:05:36.790 --> 00:05:39.550
you then need to complete a
set of documents that

00:05:39.550 --> 00:05:43.500
among other things approve the
bylaws of the company.

00:05:43.500 --> 00:05:45.870
It creates a board of
directors,

00:05:45.870 --> 00:05:47.980
it creates offices of the
company.

00:05:47.980 --> 00:05:50.110
Delaware requires that
somebody has the title of

00:05:50.110 --> 00:05:52.510
CEO or president, and of
secretary.

00:05:53.550 --> 00:05:54.990
So also at this point,

00:05:54.990 --> 00:05:58.730
you need to complete documents
that assign any inventions or

00:05:58.730 --> 00:06:01.380
any code or anything that you
as an individual create,

00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:04.520
so that the company actually
owns that.

00:06:04.520 --> 00:06:06.500
And remember at this point,
it&#39;s,

00:06:06.500 --> 00:06:08.550
it&#39;s a really good thing to
think about.

00:06:08.550 --> 00:06:09.510
You as founders have to

00:06:09.510 --> 00:06:12.520
think about things in two
different ways.

00:06:12.520 --> 00:06:14.280
You always have to be
thinking,

00:06:14.280 --> 00:06:16.250
am I doing this as an
individual?

00:06:16.250 --> 00:06:17.080
As me?

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:19.600
Or am I doing this on behalf
of the company,

00:06:19.600 --> 00:06:21.260
which is a separate entity.

00:06:21.260 --> 00:06:23.020
So you have to maintain that
split in

00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:24.760
your mind going through all of
this.

00:06:24.760 --> 00:06:27.260
And we&#39;ll talk more about
where that comes in

00:06:27.260 --> 00:06:27.980
a little bit later.

00:06:29.760 --> 00:06:33.090
So there are services that can
help you get incorporated,

00:06:33.090 --> 00:06:35.980
of course you can use a law
firm but there are also

00:06:35.980 --> 00:06:39.540
other online services that
help, and the one we often use

00:06:39.540 --> 00:06:44.620
with a lot of the YC companies
is call Clearkie Clearkie.com.

00:06:44.620 --> 00:06:46.610
And they are set up so

00:06:46.610 --> 00:06:50.650
